# Sri Anvaya

> Repository for engineering, architecture, implementation, and continuous learning.

---

## Purpose

This repository is the Single Source of Truth (SSoT) for engineering.

Chat is temporary.

The repository stores permanent knowledge.

All engineering decisions, architecture, implementation notes, and daily progress are documented here.

---

## Engineering Principles

- Build by understanding first principles.
- Learn while building.
- Prefer official documentation over tutorials.
- Build one feature at a time.
- Keep architecture simple until complexity is justified.
- Every major engineering decision must be documented.
- Every feature should leave behind permanent knowledge.

---

## Repository Structure

```
docs/
├── architecture/
├── backend/
├── frontend/
├── database/
├── api/
├── decisions/
├── learning/
└── daily/
```

---

## Development Philosophy

This project follows a feature-driven learning approach.

Each feature follows the same workflow:

```
Requirement
    ↓
First Principles
    ↓
Official Documentation
    ↓
Implementation
    ↓
Review
    ↓
Knowledge Extraction
```

---

## Documentation Rules

### Architecture

High-level engineering decisions.

### Backend

Backend architecture, APIs, authentication, integrations.

### Frontend

UI architecture, routing, rendering, state management.

### Database

Schema design, migrations, relationships, indexing.

### API

Contracts between frontend and backend.

### Decisions

Permanent engineering decisions with reasoning.

### Learning

Concepts learned while building.

Never copy official documentation.

Document only personal understanding and engineering insights.

### Daily

Daily engineering log.

---

## Engineering Standards

- Repository is the Single Source of Truth.
- Keep documentation close to implementation.
- Prefer composition over duplication.
- Document decisions, not discussions.
- Build production-quality software from the beginning.

---

## Commit Philosophy

Every commit should represent one logical unit of work.

Examples:

- docs: establish repository structure
- feat: add customer authentication
- feat: implement booking service
- refactor: simplify routing
- fix: resolve booking validation

---

